            <entry xml:id="entry_kʼaba" xml:lang="os">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>kʼaba</orth></form>
                <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                        <q>платье женское</q>
                    </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                        <q>women dress</q>
                    </abv:tr></sense>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>kʼabajag</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>материал на платье</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>material for the dress</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>moj yn k˳y wa, wæd yn kʼabatæj fyldær cy lxænʒæn</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>когда у нее будет муж, он ей будет покупать много платьев</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>when she has a husband, he will buy her many dresses</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Arsen"/><biblScope>37</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>Fatʼi ralasta kæcæjdær kʼabajag</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Фати вытащила откуда-то материал на платье</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Fati pulled out material on the dress from somewhere</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Arsen"/><biblScope>37</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>Marine jæ kʼabajy fæḱḱījæ jæ cæsty sygtæ asærfta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>Марине вытерла слезы подолом платья</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>Marine wiped her tears with the hem of her dress</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Сека"/><biblScope>95</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Из <mentioned xml:lang="ar" extralang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>qabā</w>
                        <gloss><q>верхнее платье</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar"
                        extralang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>плащ</q></gloss></mentioned>. Вероятно, через грузинское
                    посредство: <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>k’ābā</w>
                        <gloss><q>кафтан</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>платье</q></gloss></mentioned>. Вошло во многие языки Кавказа:
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/>
                        <w>a-k’aba</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sva"><lang/>
                        <w>k’ab</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/>
                        <w>ghabali</w></mentioned> и др. Сюда же <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>qaba</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Радлов"
                            /><biblScope>II 434</biblScope></bibl>). Первоисточник всей группы —
                    иранский; ср. <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>kapāh</w>
                        <gloss><q>плащ</q></gloss></mentioned>. %sВailеу%s привлекает также
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sa-vaidika"><lang/>
                        <w>kapa-</w>
                        <gloss><q>сбруя</q></gloss></mentioned> (?) и возводит к и.е. %i*kap-%i
                    ‘обхватывать’ и пр. Славянская группа слов — <mentioned xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>кабат</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cs" extralang="pl"><lang/>
                        <w>kabat</w></mentioned> и пр.— восходит к тому же источнику, но через
                    греческое посредство (<mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>καβάδης</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Berneker"
                            /><biblScope>464</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Lokotsch"/><biblScope>77</biblScope></bibl>).%n<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>53, 87,
                        519</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><author>Bailey</author><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_TPhS"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1954, стр.
                            146—153</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1954, p.
                        146—153</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">From <mentioned xml:lang="ar" extralang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>qabā</w>
                        <gloss><q>coat</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ar"
                        extralang="fa"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>raincoat</q></gloss></mentioned>. Probably, through the Georgian
                    agency: <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><lang/>
                        <w>k’ābā</w>
                        <gloss><q>caftan</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ka"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>dress</q></gloss></mentioned>. It entered many Caucasian
                    languages: <mentioned xml:lang="ab"><lang/>
                        <w>a-k’aba</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sva"><lang/>
                        <w>k’ab</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/>
                        <w>ghabali</w></mentioned> etc. <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/>
                        <w>qaba</w></mentioned> is related to it as well (<bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Радлов"/><biblScope>II 434</biblScope></bibl>). The primary
                    source of all group is Iranian; cf. <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>kapāh</w>
                        <gloss><q>raincoat</q></gloss></mentioned>. %sВailеу%s attracts also
                        <mentioned xml:lang="sa-vaidika"><lang/>
                        <w>kapa-</w>
                        <gloss><q>harness</q></gloss></mentioned> (?) and traces it back to
                    Indo-European %i*kap-%i ‘embrace’ etc. Slavic word group — <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ru"><lang/>
                        <w>кабат</w></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="cs" extralang="pl"><lang/>
                        <w>kabat</w></mentioned> etc. — traces to the same source, but through the
                    Greek agency (<mentioned xml:lang="grc"><lang/>
                        <w>καβάδης</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Berneker"
                            /><biblScope>464</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_Lokotsch"/><biblScope>77</biblScope></bibl>).%n<bibl><ref
                            type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>53, 87,
                        519</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><author>Bailey</author><ref type="bibl"
                            target="#ref_TPhS"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">1954, стр.
                            146—153</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">1954, p.
                        146—153</biblScope></bibl>.</etym>
